# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key_here
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_publishable_key_here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Edge Function secrets (NOT frontend / Vercel env vars)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Transactional email is sent by the Supabase Edge Functions (Deno), so these
# must be set as Supabase secrets, e.g.:
#   npx supabase secrets set BREVO_API_KEY=xkeysib-... --project-ref <ref>
# A BREVO_API_KEY set in Vercel is NOT visible to the edge functions.
#
#   BREVO_API_KEY      (required)  Brevo transactional API key (Brevo > SMTP & API > API Keys)
#   BREVO_FROM_EMAIL   (optional)  Sender on your Brevo-authorised domain. Default: no-reply@mymedinfo.info
#   BREVO_FROM_NAME    (optional)  Sender display name. Default: MyMedInfo
#   APP_BASE_URL       (optional)  Base URL used in email links. Default: https://www.mymedinfo.info
#
# First-owner bootstrap (leave UNSET in normal operation):
#   BOOTSTRAP_ADMIN_EMAILS  Comma-separated emails allowed to self-promote to the
#                           first owner, and ONLY while no owner/admin exists yet.
#                           Set it to seed/recover the first owner, then unset it.
